LAGOS – The stage is now set for Sir Ademola Adegoke, Ogunsusi (Knight of Charles Wesley) aka Sir Demola to embark on a musical tour of the United States of America and Canada. Sir Demola, who has five albums to his credit, has performed to the admiration of both the new and the older generation. He’s a Highlife/Juju performing and recording music artist with five albums to his credit, titles of album, Good News; All My Praise; Okunkun E ye wa; Lifted & Grateful and Fanz Danz. Over the years, he’s performed to the admiration of both the new and the older generation which has earned him numerous awards both locally and internationally. This talented musician started his international music tour with a show tagged ‘Sir Demola Suzi Live in Dubai,’ held in 2015 followed up with his America tour 2017/18 which was powered by international showbiz promoter, Sammek. Shedding more lights on the tour, the trip’s organiser, Samuel Ekundayo, CEO of USbased Sammek Moments Arts and Cultural Entertainment, said it was organised to promote the arts and culture. He also confirmed that six artists have been billed to also perform on the tour including Laolu Gbenjo, Babatunde Balogun (Saxtee vibes), Boye Best, Amb. Segun Nabi, Demola Suzi and Dele Gold. According to him, Sammek disclosed that the first leg of the musical tour will see them perform dexterously at the following events and carnivals: Alujo Nite at Atlanta Event Centre Opera; Annual AHBCA Award at Expo Event Centre, Houston, Texas; Ijoko Agaba Nite at Kings Banquet Hall, Milwaukee; Ankara Nite in Texas; Annual Yoruba Cultural Festival in Howel, Miami,” he said. The Summer 2022/2023 USA/Canada tour which is in partnership with Abedorc Promotions of Chief Yinka Farinde who is based in Canada, as promised to be a great one which will expose and export Nigeria to the western world